In jQuery 3.0 ready() method is deprecated. I think it's worth mentioning.

All of the following are equivalent and call the function fn when the document is ready:

$(fn);
$().ready(fn);
$(document).ready(fn);
$("selector").ready(fn);

As of jQuery 3.0 the recommended way to add a ready handler is the first method, $(fn).
http://jquery.com/upgrade-guide/3.0/
